Task135
When you want to present one person to another, you can use the phrase Let me introduce you to [name]
(name being the person's name). For example, Let me introduce you to Daniel.
Transcript:
Sophie: Brain, let me introduce you to Tom. Tom, this is Brain. He's web developer.

Task136
This is [name] is used to present someone in a conversation. Name refers to a person's name. It's a simple and
direct way to make introductions. For example:

Daniel, this is carol. - HEre, you are telling Daniel about Carol and helping Daniel to know who Carol is.
Transcript:
